---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Ph from '../components/Ph.astro';
import LogoRow from '../components/LogoRow.astro';
import Figure from '../components/Figure.astro';
import StatBand from '../components/StatBand.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
import headshot from '../assets/photos/placeholder-headshot.svg';
---

<Base title={SITE.metaTitle} description={SITE.metaDescription}>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="figure-split">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Operating Executive &middot; Chicago</p>
          <h1 style="margin-top: 0.9rem;">Every Visionary needs an Integrator.</h1>
          <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem; font-size: 1.1rem;">
            I&rsquo;m Tom Vranas &mdash; second-seat executive and corporate fixer for founders,
            CEOs, and PE-backed companies in transition. COO, Chief of Staff, EOS Integrator: the
            person you hand the problem nobody&rsquo;s mapped. Twenty-five years, two exits, every
            seat in the building. I learn fast, fix what&rsquo;s broken, build the system that keeps
            it fixed &mdash; and work myself out of the job.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
            <a class="btn" href="/contact">Start a conversation</a>
          </p>
        </div>
        <Figure
          src={headshot}
          alt="Placeholder for a headshot of Tom Vranas"
          caption="[Headshot — drop in src/assets/photos/, then real caption: Tom Vranas, Chicago]"
          pending
          eager
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-label="Track record at a glance">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <StatBand
        stats={[
          { value: '25', label: 'Years operating' },
          { value: '2', label: 'Institutional exits' },
          { value: '3', label: 'Acquisitions integrated' },
        ]}
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--ink" aria-label="Selected transactions">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="tombstones">
        <article class="tombstone">
          <p class="tombstone__name">EVERYWHERE WIRELESS</p>
          <hr class="tombstone__rule" />
          <p class="tombstone__outcome">Acquired by MC&nbsp;Partners</p>
          <p class="tombstone__role">
            Chief of Staff, Innovation &amp; People &middot; 2021
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="tombstone">
          <p class="tombstone__name">ZENTRO INTERNET</p>
          <hr class="tombstone__rule" />
          <p class="tombstone__outcome">Recapitalized by Greystar&nbsp;Infrastructure</p>
          <p class="tombstone__role">
            Chief of Staff, Innovation &amp; People &middot; Led 3 add-on integrations &middot; 2026
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="tombstone">
          <p class="tombstone__name">BULQIT</p>
          <hr class="tombstone__rule" />
          <p class="tombstone__outcome">Co-Founder &amp; COO</p>
          <p class="tombstone__role">2025&ndash;present</p>
        </article>
        <article class="tombstone">
          <p class="tombstone__name">SUPES ACADEMY</p>
          <hr class="tombstone__rule" />
          <p class="tombstone__outcome">Acquired</p>
          <p class="tombstone__role">
            President + COO + Owner &middot; 2015
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="tombstone">
          <p class="tombstone__name">PROACT SEARCH</p>
          <hr class="tombstone__rule" />
          <p class="tombstone__outcome">Acquired</p>
          <p class="tombstone__role">
            President + COO + Owner &middot; 2015
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="tombstone">
          <p class="tombstone__name">SOLTYRA</p>
          <hr class="tombstone__rule" />
          <p class="tombstone__outcome">Acqui-hired by The Princeton&nbsp;Review</p>
          <p class="tombstone__role">Founded &middot; 2008</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What I actually do</h2>
      <p style="margin-top: 1.2rem;">
        Strong-vision leaders are usually terrible at running the machine &mdash; and they
        shouldn&rsquo;t have to be. That&rsquo;s the seat I take. I&rsquo;ve been the COO, the
        Chief of Staff, the Chief People Officer, the head of innovation, the guy who built the
        call center and ran national marketing. Not as a tourist: as the operator accountable for
        the number. That range is the point &mdash; when I walk into your company, no function is
        foreign territory, so I can diagnose what&rsquo;s actually broken instead of what my
        specialty says is broken.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: 1.2rem;">
        I&rsquo;m built for the transition, not the steady state &mdash; and I&rsquo;ll say plainly
        what most operators won&rsquo;t: I&rsquo;m not your forever manager. I&rsquo;m the one you
        send into the problem you haven&rsquo;t mapped: the post-close mess, the broken function,
        the company that grew faster than its systems. Half the time I haven&rsquo;t seen the exact
        problem before. It&rsquo;s never mattered. I learn fast, diagnose what&rsquo;s actually
        wrong, install the operating rhythm, build the team that runs it &mdash; and hand it off
        working. Fix, grow, systematize, exit. That&rsquo;s the job.
      </p>

      <div class="proof-blocks" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
        <div class="proof-block">
          <h3>Operating rhythm</h3>
          <p>
            EOS Integrator in practice, not just vocabulary. Scorecards, L10s, accountability
            charts &mdash; the boring machinery that replaces founder intuition with a company
            that runs on purpose.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="proof-block">
          <h3>Functional range</h3>
          <p>
            Took a 25-seat call center slated for shutdown and rebuilt it into a national sales and
            support engine in 90 days. Consolidated marketing from 30+ city offices into one
            national operation. Doubled headcount in under a year as people lead while cutting
            turnover. Ran innovation teams owning all systems and data. Every seat held as the
            accountable owner, not an advisor.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="proof-block">
          <h3>Integration</h3>
          <p>
            Three add-on acquisitions integrated as operating lead through the Zentro platform:
            systems, billing, people, and customers merged without breaking revenue. The deepest
            version of the same skill &mdash; making two operating realities run as one.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="proof-block">
          <h3>Exits</h3>
          <p>
            Two institutional liquidity events &mdash; the MC Partners acquisition (2021) and the
            Greystar Infrastructure-led recapitalization (2026). I know what diligence looks for
            because I&rsquo;ve sat on the sell side of it twice.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <p class="eyebrow">Companies and institutions I&rsquo;ve worked with</p>
      <LogoRow />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Have a company that&rsquo;s outgrown how it runs?</h2>
      <a class="btn" href="/contact">Start a conversation</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
